orangelight.title: Design the biased search results reporting form

comments.body:
Consider the pattern created by the Report Harmful Language form and its call to action at the record level, and what we could do to be appropriately in sync with this.

The form should explicitly include the information they are submitting, including contextual search results, search terms, parameters, facets, etc in a meaningful way.
We decided not to provide preemptive examples of biased results to users, so as not to give them stereotype threat.  While this is in the mockups linked above, we do not intend to use this language.

pdc_describe.title: Zero bytes files not migrated from pre-curation to post-curation

comments.body:
The job to move the files had failed. Retrying the job manually (as documented in #1574) fixed the problem with the `ARK_DATA.zip` file, but not with the `README.txt` presumably because that file is zero bytes.

This is another work that has a zero byte file: https://datacommons.princeton.edu/describe/works/137 and shows the same behavior.

pdc_describe.title: Better error reporting for files that aren't moving as expected

comments.body:
For now, the work-around to retry these jobs is as follow:

* Connect to the VPN
* From your machine, run the capistrano task to launch the Sidekiq console from your machine. This will open two tabs on your browser, once for each server where Sidekiq is running:
```
cap production sidekiq:console
```

* Go to the first tab that Capistrano opened (e.g. http://localhost:nnnn/describe/sidekiq/morgue) and click the "retry all" button at the bottom of the page. The jobs usually succeed when retried. (**Be careful the "delete all" button is next to the "retry all" button, don't click it**). 

* Go to the second tab that Capistrano opened (e.g. http://localhost:xxxx/describe/sidekiq/morgue) and do the same.

It is important that you access the Sidekiq interface through the tabs that the Capistrano task opened because those tabs point directly to each of the individual servers. If you go through the load balancer the retry does not work.
